 :tx/rationale "C9-AGENT-IDENTITY-GAP: The C9 agreement detection pipeline is correct but inactive on the live store because all 226 audit observations have the same AgentId (braid:user default). The root cause: when parallel subagents create observations via braid observe, they all use the default --agent braid:user. The store sees 1 agent, not 4. find_agreement_clusters correctly returns empty because agent_observation_groups finds only 1 group. THREE DESIGN OPTIONS IDENTIFIED: (1) BRAID_AGENT env var — orchestrators set it before launching subagents. Pro: simple. Con: opt-in, agents forget. (2) PID-based auto-derivation — default agent name includes process ID. Pro: automatic for parallel processes. Con: same agent across sequential CLI invocations in one shell. (3) Session-based identity — each braid session start creates a unique agent ID, all subsequent commands inherit it. Pro: aligned with existing session lifecycle. Con: requires session start ceremony. OPEN QUESTIONS: Which approach is most substrate-independent? Should multiple approaches compose (env var overrides PID overrides session)? How do we ensure agent IDs are ALWAYS set without manual ceremony? Does the session auto-detect in main.rs already provide the right hook? THESE QUESTIONS NEED RESOLUTION BEFORE IMPLEMENTATION."
